articles.description: CJ Massinburg had 24 points, 12 rebounds and five assists and Buffalo clinched the Mid-American Conference East Division title on Friday night with a 95-82 win over Bowling Green.
articles.headline: Buffalo clinches MAC East with 95-82 win over Bowling Green

articles.headline: No. 24 Nevada plays at Utah State

articles.description: Jalen Hayes scored 24 points and Oakland beat Cleveland State 82-66 on Friday night to give coach Greg Kampe his 600th career victory.
articles.headline: Oakland wins 82-66 for Kampe's 600 victory

articles.description: Isaiah Reese had 26 points and matched a career-high with six steals to lead Canisius to a 78-60 victory over Monmouth on Friday night for its sixth straight win.
articles.headline: Reese scores 26 points, leads Canisius over Monmouth 79-60

articles.description: Seth Towns had seven of his 24 points in the final 3 1/2 minutes, Christian Juzang added a career-high 21 points, and Harvard survived with a 65-58 win over Brown on Friday night.
articles.headline: Harvard beats Brown 65-58, stays tied for first in Ivy

videos.description: Zach Norvell Jr. lobs the ball up to Johnathan Williams who throws down a two-handed jam early in the first half.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Norvell, Williams connect for alley-oop slam

videos.description: Johnathan Williams grabs Josh Perkins miss and finishes at the rim with a mean one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Williams' keeps play alive with putback dunk

videos.description: Jordan Ford drives down the lane but gets caught in traffic so he throws the ball up and somehow gets the basket.
videos.headline: Ford scores wild shot for St. Mary's

videos.description: Emmett Naar throws a deep pass to Jock Landale inside the paint and he stuffs in the basket in the first half.
videos.headline: St. Mary's Landale makes wide-open dunk

videos.description: Rui Hachimura gets past three St. Mary's defenders and hits a tricky layup for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Gonzaga's Hachimura scores tough basket for and-1

videos.description: Zach Norvell goes to score a one-handed slam but Jordan Hunter gets in the air and aggressively swats the ball away.
videos.headline: St. Mary's Hunter rises up for monstrous block

videos.description: Gonzaga head coach Mark Few credits his team for following direction and dominating offensively tonight to stay well-ahead of St. Mary's throughout the game.
videos.headline: Gonzaga coach pleased with team's attention to detail
